   <title type="text">POTSHERD - Atlas of Roman Pottery</title>
   <content type="html"><![CDATA[<span style="font-size: xx-small;">[First posted in AWOL 3 June 2011. Updated 27 November 2012]</span><br /><br /><a href="http://potsherd.net/">POTSHERD<span style="font-size: x-small;"> - </span>Atlas of Roman Pottery</a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><img alt="http://potsherd.net/atlas/gallery/img/potsherd.gif" class="decoded" src="http://potsherd.net/atlas/gallery/img/potsherd.gif" /> </blockquote><blockquote><div class="onebigger"><span style="font-size: x-small;">This is a collection of pages on pottery and ceramics in     archaeology, principally of the Roman period (1st cent.  BC     - 5th cent. AD) in Britain and western Europe.   </span></div><ul><li><span style="font-size: x-small;">                     The pages include an introductory <a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/index.html">Atlas of Roman Pottery</a>,       containing descriptions and distribution maps of types of       Roman pottery (particularly types found in Britain).     </span></li><li><span style="font-size: x-small;">       The pages of the <a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/index.html">Atlas</a> describing the individual       wares can be accessed through the main menu, which lists       the wares by <a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Class/ALL/index.html">CLASS</a> (table       wares, cooking wares, transport amphoras etc) or                      <a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Source/ALL/index.html">SOURCE</a> (by province of       origin).  Links to these indices will also be found in the main       menu bar.     </span></li></ul><div class="grid_3 alpha" style="height: 94%;"> <div class="box menu">  <h2><span style="font-size: x-small;">Introduction</span></h2><ul class="menu"><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/">Home</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/">Atlas</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/publications/">Publications</a></span>    </li></ul></div><div class="box menu">  <h2><span style="font-size: x-small;">Wares</span></h2><ul class="menu"><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/ware/ALL">All wares</a></span>    </li></ul></div><div class="box menu">  <h2><span style="font-size: x-small;">Classes</span></h2><ul class="menu"><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Class/ALL">All classes</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Class/AMPH">Amphoras</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Class/TS">Terra Sigillata</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Class/COAR">Coarse wares</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Class/FINE">Fine wares</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Class/MORT">Mortaria</a></span>    </li></ul></div><div class="box menu">  <h2><span style="font-size: x-small;">Sources</span></h2><ul class="menu"><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Source/ALL">All sources</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Source/BRIT">Britain</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Source/GAUL">Gaul</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Source/GERM">Germania</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Source/HISP">Iberia</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Source/ITAL">Italy</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Source/AFRI">Africa</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/Source/ORIE">Eastern Empire</a></span>    </li></ul></div><div class="box menu">  <h2><span style="font-size: x-small;">Mapping &amp; Databases</span></h2><ul class="menu"><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/mapping/tskilns">Terra sigillata kilns</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/mapping/rbkilns">Romano-British kilns (GB)</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/mapping/jrps">JRPS Bibliography (GB)</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/types/sigillata/gallery/">Terra sigillata forms</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/concordance/nrfrc">National Roman fabric reference collection</a></span>    </li></ul></div><div class="box menu">  <h2><span style="font-size: x-small;">Other topics</span></h2><ul class="menu"><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/topics/tools">Tools</a></span>    </li><li>      <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://potsherd.net/atlas/topics/scanning">Sherd scans</a></span>    </li></ul></div></div></blockquote>]]></content>
